gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Kings 135, Raptors 130
gameRecap.excerpt: Despite being outscored 73-58 in the second half, the Kings defeated the Raptors 135-130 and improve to 21-13 on the year. Domantas Sabonis led the Kings with 24 points, 15 rebounds, and 11 assists as DeAaron Fox added 24 points and four assists. Scottie Barnes led Toronto with 20 points, four rebounds, and six assists as Immanuel Quickley added 20 points, five rebounds, and eight assists. The Raptors move to 14-21 with the loss.
